<h2 id="editors-notes">Editorâ€™s notes</h2>

<p>As I took the first steps into learning â€œSultans of Swingâ€, one of the things that jumped out immediately was this incredibly recognizable chorus lick - and how playing it by itself can be an entirely satisfying exercise. After spending some time with it, I decided to craft some constraints around it: specifically, introducing the challenge of only using 3 strings to play all of the necessary chords.</p>

<p>While this may seem like a challenging constraint, it actually makes the lick a bit more accessible, in my opinion - it allows you to avoid any â€œfullâ€ barre chords that require 5 or 6 strings. As such, I present to you this quick warm-up exercise based on this riff. Itâ€™s a great one to memorize to turn heads wherever you may find yourself with a guitar, and likewise will help you develop barre chord muscles if you havenâ€™t yet mastered the 5- or 6-string barre. Enjoy!</p>

