<p>Although this riff requires you to only 3 strings per each chord, itâ€™s worth understanding the â€œfullâ€ version of these very same chords. Doing so will help you develop â€œbarre chord visionâ€ (as I call it), wherein youâ€™re able to recognize the full 5- or 6-string chord shapes from which you may play 2, 3, or 4 strings.</p>

