<h2 id="playing-the-3-string-chord-shapes">Playing the 3-string chord shapes</h2>

<p>Given the full chord shapes above, hereâ€™s how I recommend playing the 3-string versions of each chord as follows. For the D-minor, ideally keep your left index finger free â€“ this lets you (eventually) use it to barre the 5th fret, which is useful for both the 3-string C-major and the full 5-string D-minor.</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>E â€“â€“â€“â€“â€“â€“â€“
B â€“â€“â€“6â€“â€“â€“ &lt;== left middle
G â€“â€“â€“7â€“â€“â€“ &lt;== left pinky
